replies.text:
@DarrenMarsh-kx8hd
Season 4 was solid.
I wish they remembered Argyle, so he would’ve been in season 5!

@GraceF-j3t Yeah, Will was definitely afraid because he is gay. Not because he experienced a traumatic event as a kid, is confronted with the fact that mind bending monsters exist and has seen people he knows die.
See, this narrative of Will having to overcome his gayness to be able to defeat Vecna is effing bizarre. None of the other kids have to overcome that. Vecna is targeting the other kids because kids are easy to manipulate in general. Seems like he doesn't need them to be gay at all.

Tho, I would have liked to see it play out. I would have liked the party go fight Vecna and Vecna pointing at Will telling the others "That guy is gay." That'd be an amazing use of Will's fear of coming out. For once someone would have finally gone there to back up the narrative of weaponizing fear of coming out.

@Angel-vf4ik The trajectory of Stranger Things makes more sense to me now, knowing the Duffer brothers stole the entire show from 2 writers named Charlie Kessler and Jeffery Kennedy. Kessler pitched season 1 to them of his show called Montauk in 2014 at the Tribeca film festival, complete with series bible. At first they didn’t even change the names or the locations. Netflix wrote a huge check to him make them go away. They should have hired them instead.

Now this sort of thing happens all the time. But Charlie and Jeffery had receipts, notes, concept art and anecdotes about how it all came to be. The Duffer brothers had nothing. Judges sent both cases to a jury and Netflix didn’t want the publicity of a trial or even a settlement. So they made it all quietly go away. 

This was the 3rd or 4th time the Duffers were credibly accused of stealing screenplays. Seasons 2 - 5 are all the proof I really need to believe that they didn’t originate this.
